-- Romanian Utility Seeks Funding to Upgrade Water, Sewage System
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-10-03T14:38:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/romanian-utility-seeks-funding-to-upgrade-water-sewage-system.html
Apa-Canal Ilfov SA, a Romanian water
utility, is seeking about 6.7 million euros ($8.7 million) in
funding to upgrade a water and sewage system near the capital
Bucharest.  The utility is asking for bids from financial institutions
for a revolving  credit line  for upgrading water works in Ilfov
county as the bidding deadline expires on Oct. 30, a  European
Union procurement document showed.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
